WorldStage NewsOnline—- Nigeria’s President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the postponement of the national sports festival (NSF), tagged Edo 2020, as a precaution against the spread of coronavirus in the country. The sports festival was scheduled to take place from March 22 to April 1, 2020. Sunday Dare, minister of youth and sports development, disclosed the president’s decision via his Twitter handle on Tuesday. ”Following the briefing of Mr. President from myself and the Minister of state for Health on COVID-19, Mr President approved the immediate postponement of Edo sports festival to a future date,” Dare said. Nigeria on Tuesday confirmed a third case of COVID-19.